This paper is primarily focused on malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new approach that uses machine learning techniques, specifically neural networks, to improve the performance of malware detection. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the retraining of the model, which could be considered a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect. Finally, the paper uses evolutionary optimization, which is a type of optimization algorithm commonly used in neural networks, suggesting that it could also be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE).
